Description: Body sherd of Attic black-figured pottery closed vessel, amphora or oinochoe; exterior: black-figure decoration consisting of part of two female figures dancing or running; figure on left standing frontal and looking to right with added red on skirt; added white for flesh, mostly on the clay ground.
Curator's comments: Object owned and held by the Ashmolean Museum, Oxford. This record is included in the British Museum database as part of the Museum’s Naukratis Project, a research collaboration that aims to virtually re-unite finds from the ancient port city of Naukratis, now distributed over 80 museums worldwide.
Bibliographic references: Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p. 471, no. B808)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0101) (Phase 1)
Previous owner: Currently owned by: Ashmolean Museum, University of Oxford
